<TITLE> Bakhrabad gas pipeline catches fire </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Sept 11 (bdnews24.com)  A Bakhrabad gas transmission pipeline running through the Karnaphuli River caught fire Tuesday night, officials and witnesses said. Energy secretary AMM Nasiruddin told bdnews24.com that officials rushed to the spot. The site of the incident was somewhere near the Kalurghat Bridge. The trigger in the fire could not be known immediately, but an engineer said there were "some faults with the pipeline". Officials with the regional office of Bakhrabad Gas Systems Limited, a company of Petrobangla, said engineers are struggling to control the fire, which was spotted at 8:30pm. Bakhrabad engineer Mohammad Nahid told bdnews24.com that it appeared to be taking more time to control the fire. Witnesses said the fire spread panic in the neighbourhood. bdn
